description: Ultrafiltration (uf) is a type of membrane filtration in which hydrostatic pressure forces a liquid against a semipermeable membrane . A semipermeable membrane is a thin layer of material capable of separating substances when a driving force is applied across the membrane . Can ultrafiltration remove bacteria - a microfiltration filter has a pore size around 0.1 Micron, so when water undergoes microfiltration, many microorganisms are removed , but viruses remain in the water. Ultrafiltration would remove these larger particles, and may remove some viruses. As such the filters have no warranty as the life of filter depends on usage or hardness of water which may differ from place to place and also the above said two parameters cannot be monitored.

Follow the steps stated below to clean copper utensils.To clean a vessel from inside just squeeze  half lemon into the glass and add 1 tablespoon of salt with ½ cup of water or you can also use pitambari powder instead of lemon and salt.Close the lid and shake the mixture thoroughly.Now pour the mixture and rinse the vessel with water.Don't use a metal scrubber as copper is a soft  metal , it can cause scratches on its surface.
